race.comment: SONECHKA (5) has been finding the line well of late, the latest offering a respectable fourth over 1350m at Doomben after coming from next to last in the early stages. Draws the right gate and will never get a better chance to break through. MAHMOA (2) has not appeared since a moderate debut over 1240m at Ipswich six months ago. Trialling well and might have more to offer this prep with the shades going on. PINETO LAD (3) tackled this distance for the first time last start and did a good job to work home into fifth after a poor getaway. Faces a softer assignment today and can win without surprising. DA SILVA GOLD (6) has failed to threaten in her two runs this prep but drops 4kgs after the claim in what looks an easier race. Might be ready to show something.
